# KubeExplorer — Engineering Plan

## Project Overview

KubeExplorer is a desktop application for browsing and managing Kubernetes pod filesystems visually, similar to Windows File Explorer.

The application should allow users to:

* Browse Kubernetes clusters
* Browse namespaces
* Browse pods and containers
* Explore container filesystems
* Upload/download files
* Drag & drop files
* Edit/view files
* Open interactive terminal sessions
* Stream logs
* Work with multiple clusters

The UX goal is:

> “Windows Explorer for Kubernetes”

---

# Primary Goal

Replace workflows like:

```bash
kubectl exec -it pod -- sh
kubectl cp
kubectl logs -f
```

with a modern visual interface.

